Sixteen people sustained injuries after a taxi rolled on the Grayston Bridge in Sandton on Wednesday .On arrival ER24 paramedics found the taxi lying on its side in the middle of the road.According to ER24 Spokesperson Russel Meiring, three other vehicles were found on the scene which is believed that they were involved in the collision. Paramedics found several passengers from the taxi walking around the scene said Meiring. Upon assessment paramedics found that two patients had sustained moderate injuries while 14 others escaped the accident with minor injuries , added Meiring.All patients were transported to various hospitals in the area for further treatment.The cause of the accident is yet unknown.&nbsp;-TNA Reporter